node.text:
#makeup #vintage #60s 
A rare full makeup tutorial from 1969 narrated by makeup consultant Marla Craig. The model is Rena Alden. Though made in the late 1960's, the principles followed in this relaxing #makeuptutorial video still apply to this day. Many viewers also report that old #ASMR vibe too.
credits to: Glamourdaze on youtube.

node.title: take a look at one of my favorite 60s makeup tutorials. 💄📹 Vintage 1960s

node.text:
👑✨Princess Diana, attending her one and only MET Gala in (1996) 
dress by John Galliano . 

Princess Diana opted for a navy blue, full-length Dior slip dress, with black lace trim at the bust,  She paired it with a giant pearl choker and the look became one of her well known fashion moments.

However, according to Royal biographer Katie Nicholl, Princess Diana almost didn't wear the dress because she thought that it's 'revealing' nature might cause her then 14-year-old son William to be embarrassed.  luckily she decided to wear the dress. she was stunning.
